axation","Causes sphincter paralysis","Inhibits sphincter muscle tone"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esympathetic nervous system causes contraction of the internal urethral sphincter\u003C/strong\u003E through activation of alpha-1 adrenergic receptors on smooth muscle cells. This increases urethral resistance and helps maintain continence.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENo direct effect on the sphincter\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as there are direct sympathetic innervation and receptors.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECauses sphincter relaxation\u003C/strong\u003E occurs with parasympathetic stimulation, not sympathetic.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECauses sphincter paralysis\u003C/strong\u003E would result in complete loss of muscle tone and function.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibits sphincter muscle tone\u003C/strong\u003E would promote incontinence rather than continence.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe internal urethral sphincter is distinct from the external urethral sphincter, which is composed of skeletal muscle under voluntary control through somatic innervation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The sympathetic nervous system causes contraction of the internal urethral sphincter via alpha-1 adrenergic receptors.","Sympathetic stimulation promotes urinary continence by increasing urethral resistance.","The internal urethral sphincter is composed of smooth muscle under involuntary control."],"references":["Hall JE, Hall ME. Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology. 14th ed. Philadelphia, PA: Elsevier; 2020.","Tortora, G. J., Mellifont, R., Derrickson, B., Burkett, B., Peoples, G., D, D. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, Asia-Pacific Edition, 